Lecture and Film Show Held 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 3 (KCNA) -- A lecture was sponsored by the Poland-Korea Association on Jan. 28 on the occasion of the birthday of leader Kim Jong
Il.
 Slaboy January Guzowski, representative of the C. C., the Poland-Korea Association, in his lecture titled "On the Juche Idea and Songun Politics" explained the main reason why the DPRK remains a beacon of hope and model for the world progressives even under the complicated world situation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Thanks to the unique Songun politics of Kim Jong Il, the DPRK is demonstrating its might, standing firm against the U.S. styling itself "the world's only superpower" and stating what it wants to say, he noted. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A film show was held at Kim Jong Il Class of Kitante Primary School in Kampala on Jan. 29 under the sponsorship of the Ugandan preparatory committee for the "meeting praising the great persons of Mt. Paektu." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After watching a Korean film "Brilliant History of the Great Leadership" the school master said that the DPRK has become a politically and militarily strong country under the wise guidance of Kim Jong Il and highly praised the advantages of its educational system.

Reception Held at Syrian Embassy 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 3 (KCNA) -- Syrian Charge d'Affaires ad Interim Muhammad Adib Alhani hosted a reception at the embassy here Wednesday evening to celebrate the birthday of leader     Kim Jong Il (February 16).
 Present there on invitation were Foreign Minister Paek Nam Sun, Minister of Foreign Trade Rim Kyong Man, Minister of Education Kim Yong Jin, Vice Department Director of the C.C., the Workers' Party of Korea Pak Kyong Son, Vice-Minister of the People's Armed Forces Kim Sang Ik, Vice-Minister of Foreign Affairs Choe Su Hon, Vice-Chairman of the Committee for Cultural Relations with Foreign Countries Jon Hyon Chan, and officials concerned. 
 Alhani said in his speech that the friendly relations between Syria and the DPRK have made great progress under the deep care of leader Kim Jong Il and President Bashar al-Assad. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people have registered great success in their efforts to build a great prosperous powerful nation and reunify the country under the wise guidance of Kim Jong Il, he noted. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He expressed belief that the bilateral relations of friendship and cooperation would grow stronger in various fields in the future, too. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Paek Nam Sun in his speech said it is strong encouragement to the army and people of the DPRK accelerating the general march of the Songun revolution that close friends of Syria have expressed deep respect and reverence for Kim Jong Il, celebrating the significant February holiday together with the Korean people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The friendly and cooperative relations between the DPRK and Syria provided by President Kim Il Sung, the great leader of the Korean people, and Hafez al-Assad, the eternal leader of the Syrian people, are now growing stronger as the days go by under the deep care of the leaders of the two countries, he noted, adding that true to the noble intention of Kim Jong Il, the Korean people would strive hard to boost the friendly relationship with Syria.

Plot to Eliminate Progressive Lawmakers in S. Korea Assailed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 3 (KCNA) -- We bitterly denounce the ongoing reckless actions in south Korea to eliminate lawmakers from the Uri Party and the Democratic Workers' Party as a challenge to the south Korean people aspiring after new politics and new society and as an intolerable criminal act going against the desire of the fellow countrymen for peace and reunification of the Korean Peninsula.
 A spokesman for the Central Committee of the Democratic Front for the Reunification of the Fatherland said this in a statement on Wednesday. He continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This is nothing but a premeditated political coup to upset the balance of forces in the "National Assembly" where the ruling party holds the majority while the opposition camp minority and set the stage for the Grand National Party, a group of pro-American fascists, to grab "power" in the next term with the U.S. backing, come what may. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This coup arousing apprehension of people is a serious development that can never be overlooked by any Korean no matter where he lives, because it is aimed to block the process for independence and democracy in the south Korean society and hamstring the implementation of the June 15 North-South Joint Declaration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If the GNP and other right-wing fascist forces again dominate the NA in south Korea, it will turn into a theatre of rowdyism of the fascist gangster party and there will be the same fascist rule as was enforced in the past period of military dictatorship. In consequence, the north-south relations will be brought back to those in the era of confrontation and the holocaust of a nuclear war will be imposed upon the Korean nation.

Anti-U.S. Rally Held in Seoul 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 3 (KCNA) -- A rally for shattering the U.S. moves for a war on the Korean Peninsula and getting the U.S. troops withdrawn from south Korea was held in Seoul on Jan. 29 under the co-sponsorship of the Headquarters for the People's Movement for the Withdrawal of the U.S. Troops, the Solidarity for the Implementation of the South-North Joint Declaration, the south Korean Federation of University Student Councils (Hanchongryon) and the Solidarity of Youth and Students for the Implementation of the June 15 South-North Joint Declaration, according to a news report.
 At the rally speakers said that the plan for U.S. arms buildup is a plot to ignite a nuclear war on the Korean Peninsula and if the U.S. military base in Phyongthaek is expanded according to the plan, the military and material foundations will be laid to mount a preemptive attack on the north. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Stressing the need to foil the U.S. hard-line policy toward the north and its war moves, they declared that if the U.S. attacks the Korean nation with nukes, it will repel the aggression by the force of its great unity and Songun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A resolution read out at the rally said that neither democracy nor the people's living nor peace nor the reunification of the country can be realized as long as the U.S. domination and military presence go on. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The way out for our nation is to put an end to the 60-year-long U.S. military presence, it added. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the end of the rally deputies to Hanchongryon and students under it marched, shouting slogans "Let's enable our nation to live free from U.S. troops," "No National Security Law" and "No labeling Hanchongryon as an enemy-benefiting organization." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Song Hyo Won, chairperson of the 13th-term Hanchongryon, said it is sheer nonsense to claim that the just activities of the organization are punishable, adding that it would launch a mass struggle for the total repeal of the NSL.

Rally for Repeal of NSL and Removal of Conservative Forces Held in�@S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 3 (KCNA) -- A rally for proclaiming the February struggle for the repeal of the "National Security Law" and removal of conservative forces was held in Seoul on Jan. 29 under the sponsorship of the People's Solidarity for the Repeal of the NSL, according to a press report.
 Kwon O Hon, chairman of the Society for Supporting Prisoners of Conscience of the Family Movement for Realizing Democracy, said at the rally that the NSL is an evil law blocking the freedom of ideology and conscience and the independent reunification of the country, calling for having the evil law scrapped at the "extraordinary National Assembly session" in February without fail. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Im Pang Gyu, co-representative of Reunification Square, called for tearing up the evil law at any cost, saying the anti-reunification forces including the Grand National Party working desperately to maintain the evil law were inferior to beasts. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Song Hyo Won, chairperson of the 13th-term Hanchongryon, called upon the students to shoot the tracer shell of an all-people resistance for the repeal of the evil law, taking the van in it.

Meeting for General March of Songun Revolution Closes
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 3 (KCNA) -- The meeting for the general march of the Songun revolution, the first of its kind in the DPRK, closed Thursday after
successfully concluding its work.
 At the two-day meeting Pak Pong Ju, premier of the Cabinet, delivered a report titled "Let's dynamically step up the general march of the Songun revolution under the leadership of the great party to attain the high goal of building a great prosperous powerful nation." It was followed by speeches of more than 20 delegates of the army and various public circles who have performed shining exploits in the confrontation with the U.S. and in the drive to build a great prosperous powerful nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The meeting manifested the steadfast faith and will of the army and people of the DPRK to implement to the letter the tasks set forth in the congratulatory message of the Central Committee and the Central Military Commission of the Workers' Party of Korea under the Songun revolutionary leadership of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The message called on the participants of the meeting to display intense loyalty and devotion in making a breakthrough in a new advance and thus demonstrate the honor of being pace-setters in the general march of the Songun revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speakers vowed to resolutely foil the U.S. imperialists' moves to isolate and stifle the DPRK through the general march of the Songun revolution, open a great turning phase in carrying out the cause of building a great prosperous powerful socialist nation and glorify this as the most fruitful year in the history of the country, a year which will strikingly demonstrate the might of Songun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 An appeal to all the servicepersons and people was adopted at the meeting.

All Servicepersons and People Called upon to Speed up Gen.March of Songun Revolution
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 3 (KCNA) -- Let all the Party members, servicepersons and people turn out in the general march of the Songun revolution with
redoubled courage and vigor and wage a decisive struggle to celebrate with great pride and honor the 60th anniversaries of the foundation of the Workers' Party of Korea and the liberation of the country as grand festivals of victors and auspicious great events in the history of the nation!  This call is contained in an appeal to all the servicepersons and people adopted at the meeting for the general march of the Songun revolution which closed here Thursday.
 The appeal said: There will be a bright prospect of the country's grandeur and prosperity if we make a new charge from the forward line which we had occupied through the hard struggle waged during the "Arduous March." But, any hesitation or step back would scuttle the plan of our revolution for the eternal prosperity of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. imperialists are now making last-ditch efforts to realize their ambition to stifle the DPRK at any cost. We are now standing at the crossroads of whether we will remain eternal masters of our destiny or become slaves of imperialism. We should choose the first by launching a decisive general march.  "All for an all-out charge to glorify the 60th anniversaries of the foundation of the WPK and the liberation of the country as grand festivals of victors of the Songun revolution!" This slogan reflects the patriotic enthusiasm and revolutionary spirit of all the servicepersons and people to fully demonstrate once again the heroic spirit of Juche Korea and the might of the single-minded unity and thus bring about a great surge in all fields of the revolution and construction and a decisive turn in the building of a great prosperous powerful nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The appeal called for devotedly defending the headquarters of the revolution led by Kim Jong Il and consolidating as firm as a rock the single-minded unity of the Party, army and people with the headquarters of the revolution as its core. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It urged all to become ardent followers of the Songun idea, resolute defenders of the Songun politics and faithful implementers of the Songun line so as to remain true to the Songun revolutionary leadership of the Party. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The appeal also called for decisively frustrating the enemy's moves to destabilize the society and his psychological warfare by the force of the Songun idea, further consolidating the military base and reaching the high eminence of an economic power in the 21st century as early as possible.

Sharp Increase of Participants in Flower Festival Expected
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 3 (KCNA) -- It is expected that more and more units will participate in the forthcoming 9th Kimjongilia Festival that will be larger in scale than the last one, said Ri Pyong Pha, a department director of the Korean Kimilsungia-Kimjongilia Committee in an interview with KCNA.
 The increasing number of the participants in the traditional festival ever since its first round in Juche 86(1997) has always needed additional steps. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The 9th festival (from February 12 to 21) will be held on an unprecedented scale this year which marks the 60th anniversaries of the Workers' Party of Korea and national liberation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 More units and people in Pyongyang and local areas are still applying to the organizing committee for their participation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The festival committee plans to arrange the festival venue in a three-dimensional way so as to meet the demand of the applicants. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The forthcoming festival, which will be held to celebrate leader Kim Jong Il's birthday, will surely reflect the ardent reverence of the Korean people for him.

Mineral Medicines Made in DPRK
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 3 (KCNA) -- Researchers of Kim Il Sung University of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea have developed efficacious medicines with natural minerals abundant in the country as raw materials.
 Among them is Sindaesan which has antibiotic effect but no side-effect on liver at all.
 Its ingredients and substances good for physiological activation are helpful towards sterilization, bacteriostasis, treatment of diarrhea and inflammation, detoxication and antisepsis in human body. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It, therefore, is very potent for not only such enteric diseases as diarrhea, colitis, dysentery and intestinal tuberculosis but also food and alcoholic poisoning. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Sindaesan increases appetite, resistance to diseases and metabolism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It has been registered as an invention after it proved efficacious through clinical treatment. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The new medicines include a medicine for various kinds of skin diseases and traumatic treatment. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The sterilizer is very efficacious for inflammation, allergy, bleeding and injuries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is also good for decubitus, suppurative anusitis and colpitis. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It won a gold medal in the 8th national invention and new technology exhibition held last year.

Peasants Enjoy Holidays
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  Pyongyang, February 3 (KCNA) -- Agricultural working people of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea are enjoying holidays at rest homes under the popular policy of the Workers' Party and government.
 Director Han Myong Son of the Recreation Department of the Ministry of Labor told KCNA that peasants enjoy themselves at rest centers from December to next February every year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Leader Kim Jong Il took measures to build more modern rest homes in scenic spots to provide better recreation conditions to working people even during the "Arduous March" and the forced march. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Over the last decade, many rest homes have been built or reconstructed on an expansion basis. Among the newly built ones are the rest home for peasants in Pongsan County, North Hwanghae Province, and the Sambong rest home for working people in Thaethan County, South Hwanghae Province. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A large number of peasants are spending their holidays at rest homes in different parts of the country including the Kobangsan, Myohyangsan and Sokdamgugok Rest Centers. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 During the vacation, they visit revolutionary battle and historic sites, exchange their farming experience with each other and play colorful sports and amusement games.
